## Content

Q1 Operations Review

This memo summarizes the operations review for the first quarter of
the fiscal year. The team closed 18 of 20 planned initiatives and
flagged two items for next quarter.

Highlights

- Closed migration to the new compute trace pipeline on 2026-02-14.
- Reduced average request latency from 480 ms to 320 ms.
- Total quarterly compute spend was $48,200.50 USD against a $50,000
  budget — a $1,799.50 surplus.

Open items

- Vendor contract renewal scheduled for 2026-06-01.
- Audit report follow-up requested by audit@example.com.

Conclusion

Operations remain on track. No security incidents recorded. The next
review is scheduled for 2026-07-15.
